What you need to know:

Closer home, the talk, over the last few days, has been the heated debate over the arrival of “wavelight” pacing technology in athleticsCheptegei, 24, improved on Ethiopian legend Kenenisa Bekele’s 15-year-old record (26 minutes, 17.53 seconds) in the 25-lap race by over 6.5 seconds, clocking 26:11.00Before Cheptegei struck, another record had fallen on the Valencia track with Ethiopian Letsenbet Gidey also banking on wavelight technology to smash compatriot Tirunesh Dibaba’s 5,000m world record by almost five seconds